					<div class="post-info">
						<p>
							<span class="time">October 6, 2012</span>
															<span class="author">by <a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/author/mktgeistmike/" title="Posts by mktgeistmike" rel="author">mktgeistmike</a></span>
																						<span class="post-comments"><a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/2012/10/06/moscow-rejects-council-of-europe-resolution-over-domestic-policy-xinhuanet/#respond" title="Comment on Moscow rejects Council of Europe resolution over domestic policy&nbsp;[xinhuanet]">Leave a comment</a></span>
																				</p>
					</div>

					<p>MOSCOW, Oct. 4 (Xinhua) &#8212; Moscow is not going to follow recommendations made by the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe (PACE) regarding the state of democracy in Russia, the Kremlin said Thursday.</p>
<p>&#8220;We don&#8217;t consider these definitions and urges to be appropriate and, undoubtedly, will not bend an ear to them,&#8221; Kremlin spokesman Dmitry Peskov told local media.</p>
<p>On Tuesday, during the PACE autumn session in Strasbourg, France adopted a tough resolution calling on Russian President Vladimir Putin to democratize the political system in his country.</p>
<p>The Russian delegation in PACE, led by Alexei Pushkov, Chairman of the State Duma International Affairs Committee, failed to soften the wording of the document, local media reported.</p>
<p>&#8220;This is discrimination against the Russian Federation and a sheer example of double standards,&#8221; Alexei Pushkov told the Assembly.</p>
