<p>Syria is using a <a href="http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/06/13/us-syria-economy-money-idUSBRE85C0CL20120613?feedType=RSS&amp;feedName=topNews&amp;utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+reuters%2FtopNews+%28News+%2F+US+%2F+Top+News%29">new currency printed in Russia to pay its soaring deficit</a>, reports Suleiman Al-Khalidi of <a href="http://www.businessinsider.com/blackboard/reuters">Reuters</a>.</p>
